column370:
b"Men often do things that make women feel uncomfortable, or worse. Following the shootings in Isla Vista, California on May 23 \xe2\x80\x94 perpetrated by Elliot Rodger, a young man with a deeply misogynistic worldview \xe2\x80\x94 thousands of women took to Twitter to speak out about their experiences of fear, harassment and gender-based violence under the hashtag #YesAllWomen. The sentiments expressed are well summarized in this tweet by @AdelaideKane: \xe2\x80\x9cNot ALL men harass women. But ALL women have, at some point, been harassed by men. Food for thought.\xe2\x80\x9d
Within just a few days, #YesAllWomen had gotten over a million tweets. In their totality, the 140-character testimonies detail the presence of deep-seated and systemic violence against women in the United States and beyond. Male responses have included, as might be expected, ones of vitriol (see #NotAllMen) but also ones of solidarity and support, written under the spin-off hashtag #AllMenCan. Here are some of the most poignant comments.
@sharpegirl
	Because I wore a fake wedding ring when I waitressed. \xe2\x80\x9cBelonging\xe2\x80\x9d to another man was the only way to get customers to back off. #YesAllWomen
@stack2thefuture
	I\xe2\x80\x99d like to recommend every guy read the #YesAllWomen posts. Don\xe2\x80\x99t comment, don\xe2\x80\x99t defend. Just read and think about living in fear.
@Tuls_
	Because we cannot preach equality if we only tell the women to show less skin but never tell the men to show more respect #YesAllWomen
@NatalieCathleen
	Why do we have to remind everyone that \xe2\x80\x9cShe\xe2\x80\x99s someone\xe2\x80\x99s daughter\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9cShe\xe2\x80\x99s someone\xe2\x80\x99s wife\xe2\x80\x9d? \xe2\x80\x9cShe is someone\xe2\x80\x9d should be enough. #yesallwomen
@emaateasdalee
	Because, no means no, and I shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have to explain myself, ever.\xc2\xa0#yesallwomen
@Jcicely
	#yesallwomen because reading some responses from some men so full of disdain and vitriol is exactly the reason we need this conversation.
@RachelMcKibbens
	#YesAllWomen because after a stranger sexually harassed me in a bar, I told him the bartender was my husband, and they guy apologized TO HIM.
@TamerKattan
	#yesallwomen made me feel attacked for being male. I don\xe2\x80\x99t like it but it\xe2\x80\x99s fair and it\xe2\x80\x99s right. Read the posts. It\xe2\x80\x99ll make you a better man
@lynnbixenspan
	A man on the street told me I needed to cover up cause I was making him think impure thoughts. I was wearing a t-shirt & jeans. #yesallwomen
@HarrisonMooney
	Because the friendzone is the fictional exile of the entitled. \xe2\x80\x9cSexual partner\xe2\x80\x9d is not a woman\xe2\x80\x99s default mode. #yesallwomen
@Sean_Hollenhors
	My wife has had a self defense/escape plan since she was a teen. I cannot fathom how it feels to live like that. No man can.
@schemaly
	#YesAllWomen know what it\xe2\x80\x99s to be constantly interrupted, mocked for voicing legitimate concerns, called crazy for resisting oppression
@jessismiles__
	#YesAllWomen because even a taped confession admitting to raping me wasn\xe2\x80\x99t enough to put him in jail.
@wheresaddie
	Because men don\xe2\x80\x99t text each other that they got home safe. #YesAllWomen
@LauraLikesWine
	Because I now wear shorts under dresses in crowded bars after being groped and even penetrated by unseen hands. #YesAllWomen
@RepSpeier
	Because women serving in the military shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t fear getting raped by their colleagues more than they fear the enemy #YesAllWomen
@emilyhughes
	Because every single woman I know has a story about a man feeling entitled to access to her body. Every. Single. One. #YesAllWomen
@literaticat
	In college, we\xe2\x80\x99d regularly find girls who had been roofie\xe2\x80\x99d and left passed out in the parking lot next to our dorm. REGULARLY. #YesAllWomen
@JoyceCarolOates
	Why does the suggestion that half the human race be treated with respect by the other half arouse such fury in the latter half?#YesAllWomen
@OneBookishMom
	In college, a police officer told us to scream FIRE if we were in danger of being assaulted otherwise people won\xe2\x80\x99t get involved #YesAllWomen
@MiniiG
	Because a mans biggest blind date fear is her BMI and a woman\xe2\x80\x99s is never making it home #YesAllWomen
@peeg13
	Because when girls go to college they\xe2\x80\x99re buying pepper spray and rape whistles while guys are buying condoms #yesallwomen
@aimeemann
	The cops who asked me \xe2\x80\x9cWell, what were you wearing?\xe2\x80\x9d when I reported an attack and attempted rape. #YesAllWomen
@LuluAntariksa
	\xe2\x80\x9cMen are afraid that women will laugh at them. Women are afraid that men will kill them.\xe2\x80\x9d -Margaret Atwood #YesAllWomen
@woah_autumn
	#yesallwomen because \xe2\x80\x9cyou\xe2\x80\x99re starting to sound like a feminist\xe2\x80\x9d should not be an insult
@neilhimself
	The #yesallwomen hashtag is filled with hard, true, sad and angry things. I can empathise & try to understand & know I never entirely will.
@cmclymer
	Because as a man who writes feminist articles, I\xe2\x80\x99ve never received death or rape threats. My female colleagues? EVERY DAY. #YesAllWomen
@EmilyPuccio
	#YesAllWomen Because there\xe2\x80\x99s such a thing as a rape whistle.
@deannaraybourn
	I\xe2\x80\x99ve spent 19 yrs teaching my daughter how not to be raped. How long have you spent teaching your son not to rape? #yesallwomen
@revealedrome\xc2\xa0
	Because a smile back can get you followed, but no response can get you killed. And neither one guarantees the harassment ends. #yesallwomen
@MichaelSkolnik
	#AllMenCan stop calling women the b-word. In music, in life, in general. Fellas, we know better and must be better.
@robjones_1989
	#AllMenCan seek to understand how their actions/words either perpetuate or challenge oppressive attitudes/systems
@silvrbackgringo
	#AllMenCan listen and believe when they are told their words and actions are causing harm. You may not have \xe2\x80\x9cmeant\xe2\x80\x9d to, but you still did.
@jimmyrustlah
	#AllMenCan understand that a dress is not a yes. Women don\xe2\x80\x99t owe you anything.
@AutistLiam
	#AllMenCan Refuse to accept \xe2\x80\x9cboys will be boys\xe2\x80\x9d as an excuse for sexist or violent behavior from themselves or others.\xc2\xa0
@cmclymer
	#AllMenCan Know that yelling at women on the street is not flirting. It\xe2\x80\x99s harassment. And \xe2\x80\x9cflirting\xe2\x80\x9d after she says stop is also harassment.
@PengiunGalaxy
	#AllMenCan listen to a woman\xe2\x80\x99s story and resist the urge to challenge and unpick it in the hope that she\xe2\x80\x99s exaggerating. She probably isn\xe2\x80\x99t.
@A_McDo
	#AllMenCan accept that it\xe2\x80\x99s our job, not womens\xe2\x80\x99, to end violence against women. Challenge sexism and misogyny in all-dude conversations.
@anateboteo
	Because when I was raped my own father told me \xe2\x80\x9cwomen have been getting raped for centuries, don\xe2\x80\x99t make a big deal of it\xe2\x80\x9d #YesAllWomen
@kyoung146
	#YesAllWomen because I can\xe2\x80\x99t go running at night without being absolutely terrified
@nanglish
	Because a lot of you are reading these and thinking \xe2\x80\x9cugh yeah, we get it. Calm down.\xe2\x80\x9d #YesAllWomen
@SophiaBush
	I shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have to hold my car keys in hand like a weapon & check over my shoulder every few seconds when I walk at night #YesAllWomen
@MintMilana
	Because my friend got roofed at my Halloween party and we didn\xe2\x80\x99t report it because \xe2\x80\x9che\xe2\x80\x99s friends with everyone\xe2\x80\x9d #YesAllWomen
@lilydugas
	Here\xe2\x80\x99s to the day when I can pump gas at 10pm and not be absolutely terrified #yesallwomen
@joshgroban
	Because we all know someone who\xe2\x80\x99s been made to feel like it wasn\xe2\x80\x99t assault when it was. #yesallwomen
@scemaly
	#YesAllWomen because our bodies and reproduction are regulated like public property
@fridasbrow
	Because part of growing up was learning how to reject a man without hurting his ego so he wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t come back & do something. #yesallwomen
@schemaly
	BC when my husband asks me to slow down when we walk together I realize he hasn\xe2\x80\x99t spent his life avoiding street harassment #YesAllomen
@ginad129
	#YesAllWomen have learned how to defend themselves with their keys if they are assaulted in a parking lot
@eIectramy
	#yesallwomen because the media will mourn the lives of ruined high school football players, but not of the girls they assaulted
@katekilla
	Girls grow up knowing that it\xe2\x80\x99s safer to give a fake phone number than to turn a guy down. #yesallwomen
@Ceilidhann
	#YesAllWomen who have participated in this hashtag have steeled themselves for inevitable backlash and possible threats.
@bottrill
	#YesAllWomen because when a girl is harassed or even groped by a stranger in public, we\xe2\x80\x99re told to \xe2\x80\x9ctake it as a compliment\xe2\x80\x9d
@emilylhauser
	What is male privilege? You can choose to take a break from thinking about this. I never can. #YesAllWomen
@ZerlinaMaxwell
	#YesAllWomen because your right to your Walmart gun doesn\xe2\x80\x99t trump my right to BE ALIVE. #backgroundchecksSTAT
@michellerwiss
	Because I used to tip car drivers 40% for \xe2\x80\x9cnot raping and killing me\xe2\x80\x9d when I was in high school. #YesAllWomen
@Jcicely
	#yesallwomen because feminism and women\xe2\x80\x99s rights aren\xe2\x80\x99t a women\xe2\x80\x99s issue. They\xe2\x80\x99re human issues.
@aaroneheinz
	#AllMenCan listen and respect women\xe2\x80\x99s problems because we have NO IDEA.\xc2\xa0
@PSPandamonium
	#AllMenCan use their privilege to fight the patriarchy.
@underpope
	#AllMenCan call other men out on their sexist comments, jokes, and behaviors.
RELATED COVERAGE:\xc2\xa0
'There Was No One for Me To Turn To' by Alina\xc2\xa0Mogilyanskaya
Now All Men by Nicholas Powers
Explained by Eleanor J. Bader
"
